Babban jami'in Majalisar Dinkin Duniya ya tsallake ziyarar Pakistan, inda ya ambaci batun jirgin
ISLAMABAD (AP) - Shugaban babban zauren Majalisar Dinkin Duniya da ke shigowa ya sanar a ranar Lahadi cewa, ya aika da ziyarar da aka shirya yi a Pakistan "duka ga wasu matsalolin jirgin sama na fasaha."
An zabi babban jami'in diflomasiyyar Turkiyya Volkan Bozkir a matsayin shugaban majalisar dinkin duniya na 75 a watan da ya gabata, kuma an shirya zai isa birnin Islamabad a ranar Lahadi.
Amma a wani sakon Twitter, ya ce ziyarar zuwa babban birnin Pakistan za ta jira.
Ministan harkokin waje na Pakistan Shah Mahmood Qureshi ya fada a martanin Bozkir cewa, "Ina fatan barka da zuwa kasar Pakistan nan ba da jimawa ba don ziyarar mai kyau da ya dace."
A kwanan baya, wani mai gabatar da kara Qureshi, yayin da yake sanar da ziyarar, ya yi fatan zai tattauna batutuwa da dama da Bozkir, ciki har da Kashmir, wanda ke raba tsakanin Pakistan da makwabciyarta Indiya da kuma da'awar duka biyu.
Pakistan da Indiya sun gwabza yaƙe-yaƙe biyu daga cikin ukunsu a kan yankin da ake takaddama akai tun bayan samun 'yancin kai daga mulkin Birtaniya a 1947.
Sau da yawa bangarorin biyu sun yi musayar wuta a Kashmir, lamarin da ya sa sojoji da fararen hula suka jikkata a bangarorin biyu.
Pakistan tana son Majalisar Dinkin Duniya ta taka rawar gani wajen warware batun Kashmir a ƙarƙashin ƙudurinta ta hanyar ƙyale mutanen da ke zaune a yankin Himalayan su yanke shawarar ko suna son su haɗa kai da Indiya, da Pakistan ko kuma su fi son samun yancin kai.
